dismissalText.commentary: Will Young lbw b Varun 15 (23b 2x4 0x6 41m) SR: 65.21

dismissalComment.html: That's out lbw, looked dead. No review. Legbreak with the seam pointing towards backward point, it drifted in to land around off and hit low on the pad. Young's bat flicked the pad and missed the ball. Height and line not an issue, that is goodnight nurse. Hawk-Eye shows it'd go on to smash middle and leg. Varun pumps his fist like a boxer, slaps a high-five to KL Rahul

dismissalText.commentary: Rachin Ravindra b Kuldeep Yadav 37 (29b 4x4 1x6 52m) SR: 127.58

dismissalComment.html: Googly to clatter the stumps, a special ball to dismiss a special batter! 84ks back-of-hander landed a touch back of length around a fourth-stump line, Ravindra shaped to play on the off side but was cramped for room. He had to adjust his shot late but the pace off the pitch didn't allow him to do that, the front toe was pointing up, the bat was neither horizontal nor vertical as he tried to fend last minute; pad got tickled, top of off got smashed. Kuldeep leaps in the air, gets a headlock from Rahul, lots of hugs too. He's broken the game open with his first ball

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson c & b Kuldeep Yadav 11 (14b 1x4 0x6 19m) SR: 78.57

dismissalComment.html: Spooned back, dolly for Kuldeep. He runs back with his index finger up, gets big hugs from his team-mates, big pop from the crowd too. New Zealand's top order is gone! Stock ball was full on 82ks, around off stump, Williamson lunged across for a flick. Might've wanted to run it to long-on. Not sure if it dipped but KW seemed to be early on the shot. Played well in front of the body, lobbed it to the bowler's right. Batter shakes his head while looking back up.

dismissalText.commentary: Will Young lbw b Varun 15 (23b 2x4 0x6 41m) SR: 65.21

dismissalComment.html: That's out lbw, looked dead. No review. Legbreak with the seam pointing towards backward point, it drifted in to land around off and hit low on the pad. dismissalText.commentary: Rachin Ravindra b Kuldeep Yadav 37 (29b 4x4 1x6 52m) SR: 127.58

dismissalComment.html: Googly to clatter the stumps, a special ball to dismiss a special batter! 84ks back-of-hander landed a touch back of length around a fourth-stump line, Ravindra shaped to play on the off side but was cramped for room. He had to adjust his shot late but the pace off the pitch didn't allow him to do that, the front toe was pointing up, the bat was neither horizontal nor vertical as he tried to fend last minute; pad got tickled, top of off got smashed. Kuldeep leaps in the air, gets a headlock from Rahul, lots of hugs too. He's broken the game open with his first ball

dismissalText.commentary: Shubman Gill c Phillips b Santner 31 (50b 0x4 1x6 75m) SR: 62

dismissalComment.html: Has anyone seen Superman and Phillips in the same room? I doubt it. He has just caught another blinder. And this one really is an absolute blinder. Floated outside off, he looks to go up and over GP at short extra cover. That was a boundary if anyone else was there. Not when GP is there. He leaps, flicks out his right hand and hangs on to a stunner. Flashes a big smile right after.

Going onto hit the stumps - Oh, yes! Bracewell is pumped up and NZ suddenly have an opening

dismissalComment.html: The Squeeze. IS. ON! In fact, NZ have squeezed water out of stone. Rohit dances down and gets stumped! Huge moment, he waslks back with his head down for most of the way back. Applause from the crowd but NZ are well in the game now. First ball of the over, Rohit looked to manufacture a boundary. Was a shortish ball outside off that spun away, was a pre-meditated shot from Rohit. He charged down and tried to slap it over cover
